## Markdown Rules

### Disabled Rules

The following markdownlint rules are explicitly disabled:

- [`MD001`](https://github.com/DavidAnson/markdownlint/blob/main/doc/Rules.md#md001): Heading levels should only increment by one level at a time
- [`MD012`](https://github.com/DavidAnson/markdownlint/blob/main/doc/Rules.md#md012): Multiple consecutive blank lines
- [`MD024`](https://github.com/DavidAnson/markdownlint/blob/main/doc/Rules.md#md024): Multiple headings with the same content
- [`MD025`](https://github.com/DavidAnson/markdownlint/blob/main/doc/Rules.md#md025): Multiple top-level headings in the same document
- [`MD026`](https://github.com/DavidAnson/markdownlint/blob/main/doc/Rules.md#md026): Trailing punctuation in heading
- [`MD029`](https://github.com/DavidAnson/markdownlint/blob/main/doc/Rules.md#md029): Ordered list item prefix
- [`MD033`](https://github.com/DavidAnson/markdownlint/blob/main/doc/Rules.md#md033): Inline HTML (allowed for our XML tags)
- [`MD036`](https://github.com/DavidAnson/markdownlint/blob/main/doc/Rules.md#md036): Emphasis used instead of a heading
- [`MD037`](https://github.com/DavidAnson/markdownlint/blob/main/doc/Rules.md#md037): Spaces inside emphasis markers
- [`MD041`](https://github.com/DavidAnson/markdownlint/blob/main/doc/Rules.md#md041): First line in a file should be a top-level heading

### Heading Rules

- [`MD002`](https://github.com/DavidAnson/markdownlint/blob/main/doc/Rules.md#md002): First heading should be a top-level heading
- [`MD003`](https://github.com/DavidAnson/markdownlint/blob/main/doc/Rules.md#md003): Heading style must be ATX with space after hash: `# Heading`
- [`MD015`](https://github.com/DavidAnson/markdownlint/blob/main/doc/Rules.md#md015): No space after hash on atx style heading
- [`MD016`](https://github.com/DavidAnson/markdownlint/blob/main/doc/Rules.md#md016): No trailing punctuation in plain text headings
- [`MD017`](https://github.com/DavidAnson/markdownlint/blob/main/doc/Rules.md#md017): No space after hash on closed atx style heading
- [`MD018`](https://github.com/DavidAnson/markdownlint/blob/main/doc/Rules.md#md018): No space after hash on atx style heading
- [`MD019`](https://github.com/DavidAnson/markdownlint/blob/main/doc/Rules.md#md019): Multiple spaces after hash on atx style heading
- [`MD020`](https://github.com/DavidAnson/markdownlint/blob/main/doc/Rules.md#md020): No space inside hashes on closed atx style heading
- [`MD021`](https://github.com/DavidAnson/markdownlint/blob/main/doc/Rules.md#md021): Multiple spaces inside hashes on closed atx style heading
- [`MD022`](https://github.com/DavidAnson/markdownlint/blob/main/doc/Rules.md#md022): Headings should be surrounded by blank lines
- [`MD023`](https://github.com/DavidAnson/markdownlint/blob/main/doc/Rules.md#md023): Headings must start at the beginning of the line
- [`MD043`](https://github.com/DavidAnson/markdownlint/blob/main/doc/Rules.md#md043): Required heading structure
- Maximum depth: 4 levels

<example>
# Main Title
## Section
### Subsection
</example>

<example type="invalid">
#No Space
## Section
#### Skipped Level
</example>

### List and Indentation Rules

- [`MD004`](https://github.com/DavidAnson/markdownlint/blob/main/doc/Rules.md#md004): Unordered list style must be consistent
- [`MD005`](https://github.com/DavidAnson/markdownlint/blob/main/doc/Rules.md#md005): List indentation must be consistent
- [`MD006`](https://github.com/DavidAnson/markdownlint/blob/main/doc/Rules.md#md006): Start bulleted lists at the beginning of the line
- [`MD007`](https://github.com/DavidAnson/markdownlint/blob/main/doc/Rules.md#md007): Unordered list indentation (2 spaces)
- [`MD008`](https://github.com/DavidAnson/markdownlint/blob/main/doc/Rules.md#md008): No trailing spaces in lists
- [`MD030`](https://github.com/DavidAnson/markdownlint/blob/main/doc/Rules.md#md030): Spaces after list markers
- [`MD032`](https://github.com/DavidAnson/markdownlint/blob/main/doc/Rules.md#md032): Lists should be surrounded by blank lines

### Link and Reference Rules

- [`MD011`](https://github.com/DavidAnson/markdownlint/blob/main/doc/Rules.md#md011): No reversed link syntax
- [`MD034`](https://github.com/DavidAnson/markdownlint/blob/main/doc/Rules.md#md034): No bare URLs
- [`MD039`](https://github.com/DavidAnson/markdownlint/blob/main/doc/Rules.md#md039): No spaces inside link text
- [`MD042`](https://github.com/DavidAnson/markdownlint/blob/main/doc/Rules.md#md042): No empty links
- [`MD051`](https://github.com/DavidAnson/markdownlint/blob/main/doc/Rules.md#md051): Link fragments should be valid
- [`MD052`](https://github.com/DavidAnson/markdownlint/blob/main/doc/Rules.md#md052): Reference links and images should use a label that is defined
- [`MD053`](https://github.com/DavidAnson/markdownlint/blob/main/doc/Rules.md#md053): Link and image reference definitions should be needed
- Use descriptive link text
- Prefer relative paths for internal links
- Include title attributes for external links

<example>
[Installation Guide](./docs/install.md)
[TypeScript Docs](https://www.typescriptlang.org/ "TypeScript Documentation")
</example>

<example type="invalid">
[Click Here](./file.md)
[https://example.com](https://example.com)
</example>

### Code Block Rules

- [`MD031`](https://github.com/DavidAnson/markdownlint/blob/main/doc/Rules.md#md031): Fenced code blocks should be surrounded by blank lines
- [`MD038`](https://github.com/DavidAnson/markdownlint/blob/main/doc/Rules.md#md038): No spaces inside code span elements
- [`MD040`](https://github.com/DavidAnson/markdownlint/blob/main/doc/Rules.md#md040): Fenced code blocks must have a language specified
- [`MD046`](https://github.com/DavidAnson/markdownlint/blob/main/doc/Rules.md#md046): Code block style must be consistent
- [`MD048`](https://github.com/DavidAnson/markdownlint/blob/main/doc/Rules.md#md048): Code fence style must be consistent
- Include code comments when needed

<example>
```typescript
function greet(name: string): void {
  // Log greeting to console
  console.log(`Hello, ${name}!`);
}
```

Reference the `greet()` function.
</example>

